## gRPC Stream-Specific Strategies

### Problem: Streams Pin to Endpoints
A server-streaming RPC (like event.OnEvent) lives on one endpoint forever.
If that endpoint degrades, the stream suffers but doesn't move.

### Strategy 1: Weighted New Connections
Shift weight away from degraded endpoints. New streams land elsewhere.
Existing streams stay until natural close or timeout.

### Strategy 2: Graceful Drain via GOAWAY
Envoy can send HTTP/2 GOAWAY to a backend, causing it to stop accepting
new streams and close existing ones gracefully. The AI Router triggers
this when an endpoint needs to be evacuated.

### Strategy 3: Stream-Aware Health Checking
Track stream duration per endpoint. If one endpoint has streams that
are abnormally long (10x median), it might be stuck. Flag for
investigation rather than auto-action (streams are business logic).

### Strategy 4: Max Concurrent Streams
Set `max_concurrent_streams` per endpoint via circuit breakers.
Prevents one endpoint from accumulating too many long-lived streams
while others sit idle.

